We have to convert given tree into a string and string back into the tree this ois called serialization and deserialization.

We will do this with the recursive functions. We use preorder traversal.

Algorithm:
Step 1:
Use preorder traversal to serialize the tree.

Preorder means:
root -> left -> right

Step 2:
If the current node is null, add "null," to the string.

Step 3:
If the current node is not null:
add node value,
serialize left subtree,
serialize right subtree.

Step 4:
For deserialization, convert the string into a list.

Step 5:
Read the list from left to right.

If the first value is "null":
remove it and return null.

Otherwise:
create a TreeNode using the first value,
remove that value,
recursively build the left subtree,
recursively build the right subtree.

Step 6:
Return the rebuilt root.




public class Codec {

    public String recserialize(TreeNode root, String str) {
        if (root == null) {
            str += "null,";
        } else {
            // Preorder: root, left, right
            str += root.val + ",";
            str = recserialize(root.left, str);
            str = recserialize(root.right, str);
        }

        return str;
    }

    // Encodes a tree to a single string.
    public String serialize(TreeNode root) {
        return recserialize(root, "");
    }

    public TreeNode recdeserialize(List<String> str) {
        // Null marker means no node here
        if (str.get(0).equals("null")) {
            str.remove(0);
            return null;
        }

        TreeNode root = new TreeNode(Integer.valueOf(str.get(0)));
        str.remove(0);

        // Build left and right using the remaining values
        root.left = recdeserialize(str);
        root.right = recdeserialize(str);

        return root;
    }

    // Decodes your encoded data to tree.
    public TreeNode deserialize(String data) {
        String[] strArray = data.split(",");
        List<String> list = new LinkedList<>(Arrays.asList(strArray));

        return recdeserialize(list);
    }
}
